Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I noticed they looked like regular blue pills.

Speaker 2: Yeah, just go ahead and throw those in the trash can.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I just put in the correct order that will be shipped out to you today.

Speaker 2: So when you get this new bottle, on the bottle it's going to say AGV, but it's also going

Speaker 1: to say Greenstone.

Speaker 2: Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 1: And then on the pills, the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100 for the milligrams.

Speaker 2: And those are the two ways you can confirm you received the FDA-approved AGV, because

Speaker 1: right now your bottle says APCO, and on your pills it says AC 340 or 390 or something like

Speaker 2: that.

Speaker 1: And then I'm going to go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 2: I'm going to pause it until July 31st of 2026, because if I cancel you out now, it's

Speaker 1: going to delete your profile, and the pharmacy won't be able to send you that replacement.

Speaker 2: And I'm going to give you my extension, so you can call me back and let me know how the

Speaker 1: AGV works out for you.

Speaker 2: Okay, next question is, am I going to be charged this time?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: No, because you received the incorrect medication.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Hang on, let me get a pen.

Speaker 2: Yeah, take your time.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, it's 0020, and my name is Michelle.

Speaker 1: I sure appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, of course, Steve.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry about that.

Speaker 2: Sometimes that happens because it's in such high demand, but they don't tell us, which

Speaker 1: is a great spot.

Speaker 2: Go ahead.

Speaker 1: Well, at least you handled it correctly, so I'll give it another shot.

Speaker 2: All right, perfect.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and then you have my extension, so you don't have to wait on hold.

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: Awesome.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Michelle.

Speaker 1: All right, you have a great day.

Speaker 2: No problem, Steve.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Bye.
